## TESTING

- Use **Vitest** + **React Testing Library** (RTL)
- Test behaviour, not implementation — query by role/text/label, never by class or component name
- One test file per component: `UserCard.test.tsx` next to `UserCard.tsx`
- Always test: default render, prop variations, user interactions, error and empty states

```tsx
// ✅ Test what the user sees
test('shows delete button only when editable', () => {
  render(<UserCard user={mockUser} isEditable />)
  expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /delete/i })).toBeInTheDocument()
})

// ❌ Never test implementation details
expect(wrapper.state().isDeleting).toBe(true)
```

- Mock API/backend calls at the module level, not inside individual tests
- Avoid snapshot tests — they catch nothing meaningful and break constantly

---

## ERROR HANDLING

- Every data-fetching component must handle `error` and `isLoading` states explicitly
- Use React Query's `error` object, not try/catch in components
- Use an `ErrorBoundary` at the route/page level to catch unexpected render errors
- Surface user-friendly error messages via shadcn `Toast` — never raw `alert()`
